  "prompt": "How does international law intersect with national laws on money laundering?",
  "response": "International law intersects with national money laundering laws in several key ways:\n\n1. Global Regulatory Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n\n2. Compliance Requirements\n- Standardized due diligence procedures\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Cross-border information sharing\n\n3. Legal Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Extradition agreements\n- Asset seizure and recovery protocols\n- Coordinated investigations\n- Sanctions against non-compliant jurisdictions\n\n4. Technological Coordination\n- Information exchange platforms\n- Digital tracking of financial transactions\n- Harmonized anti-money laundering (AML) technologies\n\n5. Jurisdictional Cooperation\n- Mutual legal assistance\n- Shared investigative resources\n- Consistent legal standards\n- Transnational prosecution strategies\n\n6. Risk Management\n- International risk assessment frameworks\n- Uniform classification of financial crimes\n- Collaborative monitoring systems\n\nThese intersections create a complex, multilayered approach to combating money laundering globally.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these specific aspects?",
